post_text: Our much anticipated, 2019-20 Yearbooks have just arrived! We will begin sending yearbooks home with students attending in-person, on Tuesday 9/1. Virtual families, are able to pick up your pre-purchased 2019-20 yearbook beginning Wednesday 9/2, Thursday 9/3 from 8:00am-2:30pm and again on Tuesday 9/8, Wednesday 9/9 and Friday 9/11 from 8:00am-2:30pm. We will mail yearbooks out to students not currently enrolled at WPCA, that have pre-purchased last year's yearbook, beginning Monday 8/31-Tuesday 9/8. Any yearbooks that have not been picked up by September 15th will be mailed at that time to the families who pre-ordered them. Unfortunately, no additional yearbooks were ordered, therefore we will not have any yearbooks available for purchase at the school.

We miss you and are so excited to welcome you back to school this fall! We are planning for a school year of learning together in an in-person classroom environment. However, we realize things can change between now and the first day of school. Take a moment to watch this video to hear more about how we’re preparing for the 2020-21 school year. We created detailed plans around four learning scenarios. These plans are in-line with our state's department of education plan, which outlines required and recommended safety protocols for the 2020-21 school year based on the status of coronavirus in our community.
For the most up to date information on back to school plan, please visit: https://www.nhaschools.com/en/COVID-19

Learn more about our Moral Focus program from Mr. Greiner our Middle School Dean! "When everyone is using these virtues, it makes our schools safe, caring places to learn and grow. Outside the classroom, it reinforces the strong moral values that help children interact with their friends, families, and communities with respect and care."

For the month of April, the Moral Focus virtue is Compassion. Compassion is to care for and support others when they need help.

Check out his website for fun family activites to practice compassion: https://www.naturespath.com/en-us/blog/17-activities-kids-practice-kindness-compassion/

post_text: This scholar uses his saved scholar dollars to be principal for an hour. He passed out scholar dollars to students who were following expectations in the hallway. He inspected the bus before our 8th graders left for a field trip. He made an all school announcement. Telling the scholars that it was too cold to go outside for recess. He fixed the jammed copier machine and ran his first leadership meeting. Whew, what a busy hour it was!! #PBIS in action. #wecelebratestudents

post_text: Windemere Park Charter Academy is a tuition-free public charter school open to all students in Michigan. Our program not only follows state standards, but offers a great college-prep education and custom-created moral focus program. Founded in 1999 by members of your community, we work tirelessly to give parents a better choice.
